 My dad was diagnosed with follicular lymphoma about a month ago. I Think we are still in the staging part of all this. 
Yesterday, he showed me his bone marrow biopsy results : " a few clusters of hematropoietic components with 3 cell lineage maturation;
Erythroid cells appear hyperplastic;
Lack of cellularity precludes further evaluation"
He didn't understand it. His Doctor has suggested daily radiation for a month, and discussed that with him, but did not explain the biopsy. Does anyone know if these results are 'normal', or expected or not? My dad is   77, and seems in fairly good health otherwise.
